<div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane box box-primary" id="fees">
	<h2>Fees and Payment</h2>
	<h4><strong> Fees for permission.— </strong></h4>	
	<ol>
		<li>No application, petition, notice or appeal to the Authority in respect of permission for any development  or  sale  of  land  shall  be  considered  valid  by  the  Authority  unless  and  until and the person giving the notice has paid the processing fees as per Schedule appended to these rules to the Authority.  Provided that Central and State Govt. and the local Authority need not pay this application fees; Provided further that these shall be payable only once in  respect  of  a  particular  application  etc.  until  it  is  disposed  of  by  the  Authority  and  in relation to that particular application. </li>
		<li>In  the  event  of  any  doubt  or  dispute  about  any  question  relating  to  application  fees  the Authority’s decision shall be final.</li>
		<li>Rate of application fees for erection of new residential building (including group housing,institutional building  religious, cultural etc.) are as given in Schedule  VII. All other fees shall also be charged as prescribed in Schedule VII</li>
		<li>Application fees for re-erection, addition or alteration of an existing building shall be same as for erection of a new building prescribed in sub-rule. </li>
	</ol>
	
</div>